⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Dream of the Mare
node CRP · CRP · ⟦The Dream of the Mare:CRP:7f8ecd⟧

WHO   — The Dream of the Mare — the beaten horse
WHAT  — The conscience speaking before the crime: the dreaming child weeps and embraces the dead horse, the part of Raskolnikov that knows.
WHERE — CRP · Crime and Punishment  Framework inputs: Crime and Punishment (Dostoevsky, 1866)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the unconscious sees what the theory denies — that cruelty is unbearable, and that he is the weeping child, not the man with the whip.
HOW   — By the grammar of dream — a memory of childhood pity surfacing to warn him off the murder he is rationalising awake.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the child in you who runs to the beaten mare and kisses its dead mouth — the pity the theory swore you had outgrown.

